Example 4.3.1 from Experimental Design & Analysis for Tree Improvement

Source: R/Exam4.3.1.R
Exam4.3.1.Rd

Exam4.3.1 presents the germination count data for 4 Pre-Treatments and 6 Seedlots.

References

  1. Williams, E.R., Matheson, A.C. and Harwood, C.E. (2002).Experimental Design and Analysis for Tree Improvement. CSIRO Publishing.

See also

DataExam4.3.1

Examples

data(DataExam4.3.1)
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
fm4.4    <- aov(
 formula     = Percent~Replication+Pretreatment*SeedLot
 , data      = DataExam4.3.1
  #, subset
  #, weights
  #, na.action
 , method      = "qr"
 , model       = TRUE
 , x           = FALSE
 , y           = FALSE
 , qr          = TRUE
 , singular.ok = TRUE
 , contrasts   = NULL
 )
 anova(fm4.4)
#> Analysis of Variance Table
#> 
#> Response: Percent
#>                      Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value    Pr(>F)    
#> Replication           2     16     8.2  0.0239  0.976409    
#> Pretreatment          3  51266 17088.8 49.6447 1.822e-14 ***
#> SeedLot               5   6228  1245.6  3.6185  0.007642 ** 
#> Pretreatment:SeedLot 15   2788   185.9  0.5400  0.903453    
#> Residuals            46  15834   344.2                      
#> ---
#> Signif. codes:  0 ‘***’ 0.001 ‘**’ 0.01 ‘*’ 0.05 ‘.’ 0.1 ‘ ’ 1

 DataExam4.3.1 %>%
   dplyr::group_by(Pretreatment) %>%
   dplyr::summarize(Mean=mean(Percent))
#> # A tibble: 4 x 2
